00:42:07,565 --> 00:42:08,854
Got you.

536
00:42:08,854 --> 00:42:11,521
(Mary coughing)

537
00:42:13,444 --> 00:42:14,361
- You okay?

538
00:42:21,325 --> 00:42:22,290
You okay?

539
00:42:22,290 --> 00:42:23,123
- Yeah.

540
00:42:29,670 --> 00:42:32,673
- I got a letter today
from that guy in prison.

541
00:42:33,690 --> 00:42:34,790
- Oh, I wanna read it.

542
00:42:36,660 --> 00:42:37,493
- Tore it up.

543
00:42:56,618 --> 00:42:57,451
(ambulance siren)

544
00:42:57,451 --> 00:42:59,451
- Yeah, I got your page.

545
00:43:01,110 --> 00:43:02,373
Okay, I'm on my way.

546
00:43:03,984 --> 00:43:06,901
(eerie jazz music)

547
00:43:19,198 --> 00:43:22,365
(indistinct shouting)

548
00:43:40,320 --> 00:43:43,383
- [Samuel] Dear Penny, thank
you for writing me back.

549
00:43:45,330 --> 00:43:49,413
It's funny, I never expected
you to be so cheerful.

550
00:43:51,210 --> 00:43:52,960
You asked me what my interests are.

551
00:43:54,360 --> 00:43:57,783
To tell the truth, I
don't really know anymore.

552
00:43:59,190 --> 00:44:01,980
I was a mechanic before
they put me in here.

553
00:44:01,980 --> 00:44:04,590
But if my appeal comes
through and I get out,

554
00:44:04,590 --> 00:44:05,823
I won't go back to that.

555
00:44:07,470 --> 00:44:10,857
To answer your second
question, "What's prison like?"

556
00:44:12,990 --> 00:44:13,893
It's lonely.

557
00:44:25,837 --> 00:44:28,470
- [Mary] "Rules fail. Breaking apart.

558
00:44:28,470 --> 00:44:31,143
Falling down and coming undone.

559
00:44:32,010 --> 00:44:33,753
Galaxies collide.

560
00:44:34,920 --> 00:44:37,173
The simplest molecule prevails.

561
00:44:38,610 --> 00:44:41,943
