me, why are you in prison?

567
00:45:05,746 --> 00:45:08,663
(waterfall rushes)

568
00:45:13,061 --> 00:45:16,644
(indistinct radio chatter)

569
00:45:34,969 --> 00:45:37,886
(stone taps glass)

570
00:45:45,878 --> 00:45:46,961
- [Penny] Hi.

571
00:45:52,772 --> 00:45:56,439
I guess I don't really
have anything to say.

572
00:45:57,630 --> 00:45:59,495
This is stupid.

573
00:45:59,495 --> 00:46:02,495
- Would you like to hear some music?

574
00:46:04,463 --> 00:46:05,463
- All right.

575
00:46:07,306 --> 00:46:10,056
(muffled speech)

576
00:46:13,146 --> 00:46:15,729
(gentle music)

577
00:46:26,017 --> 00:46:27,350
- Just sit down.

578
00:46:42,208 --> 00:46:43,958
- Where are you from?

579
00:46:46,193 --> 00:46:48,693
- [Man] A forest full of snow.

580
00:46:50,824 --> 00:46:53,407
- What's that supposed to mean?

581
00:46:54,523 --> 00:46:56,106
- It was a village.

582
00:47:02,686 --> 00:47:05,269
- Does the village have a name?

583
00:47:06,900 --> 00:47:07,733
- Not anymore.

584
00:47:08,760 --> 00:47:12,297
It was burned to the
ground. There's nobody left.

585
00:47:33,990 --> 00:47:38,553
- You have beautiful eyes, but empty.

586
00:47:44,325 --> 00:47:47,550
- Well then, I guess I'm empty.

587
00:47:47,550 --> 00:47:50,673
Can we just shut up and
listen to the music?

588
00:47:59,250 --> 00:48:00,083
I'm sorry.

589
00:48:04,707 --> 00:48:07,546
(gentle music)

590
00:48:07,546 --> 00:48:10,463
(woman vocalizing)

591
00:49:32,628 --> 00:49:35,518
(Mary panting)

592
00:49:35,518 --> 00:49:38,018
(eerie music)

593
00:49:49,893 --> 00:49:51,060
- [Mary] Help.

594
00:49:56,699 --> 00:49:57,866
Help me. Help.

595
00:50:44,656 --> 00:50:45,489
- Good morning.

596
00:50:46,770 --> 00:50:48,470
You slept like a rock, little one.

597
00:50:53,070 --> 00:50:54,963
I'm sorry I got in so late.

598
00:50:56,580 --> 00:50:59,673
I was talking to your boyfriend.

599
00:51:00,810 --> 00:51:02,110
- [Mary] Did you kiss him?

600
00:51:03,780 --> 00:51:06,843
- No. Don't be silly.

601
00:51:10,140 --> 00:51:11,840
- He's wonderful though, isn't he?

602
00:51:13,110 --> 00:51:14,510
- I like how he is with you.

603
00:51:17,179 --> 00:51:18,012
- Oh, Penny.

604
00:51:19,977 --> 00:51:21,393
- "Oh Penny," what?

605
00:51:22,800 --> 00:51:24,630
What's wrong with you this morning?

606
00:51:24,630 --> 00:51:26,830
- You kind of feel numb
all over, don't you?

607
00:51:29,430 --> 00:51:30,880
- What are you talking about?

608
00:51:33,176 --> 00:51:34,626
- I did something last night.

609
00:51:36,662 --> 00:51:38,762
I thought it was because I was mad at you.

610
00:51:40,410 --> 00:51:41,763
I took one of your pills.

611
00:51:43,860 --> 00:51:45,270
- Are you crazy?

612
00:51:45,270 --> 00:51:46,500
- I never understood it before.

613
00:51:46,500 --> 00:51:50,040
How you didn't feel anything at all?

614
00:51:50,040 --> 00:51:51,720
- Are you crazy?

615
00:51:51,720 --> 00:51:53,910
Then you know what I did?
I threw them all away.

616
00:51:53,910 --> 00:51:55,530
- You had no right to do that.

617
00:51:55,530 --> 00:51:57,390
- [Mary] What do you care
about some stupid pills?

618
00:51:57,390 --> 00:51:58,840
I know you can get some more.

619
00:52:01,170 --> 00:52:03,330
- Don't turn away from me. Look at me.

620
00:52:03,330 --> 00:52:04,260
Why did you do that?

621
00:52:04,260 --> 00:52:06,180
Do you have any idea what
those could do to you?

622
00:52:06,180 --> 00:52:07,713
- [Mary] Leave me alone.

623
00:52:08,880 --> 00:52:10,263
You make me sick.

624
00:52:12,720 --> 00:52:15,373
You like how he is with me?

625
00:52:15,373 --> 00:52:17,553
Like I'm four years old.

626
00:52:18,600 --> 00:52:20,845
That's what you want, isn't it?

627
00:52:20,845 --> 00:52:22,053
Look at me.

628
00:52:22,053 --> 00:52:23,641
I'm almost 16 years old,

629
00:52:23,641 --> 00:52:27,911
and I'm nothing but a big, overgrown baby.

630
00:52:27,911 --> 00:52:29,959
- No, I don't. I didn't mean-

631
00:52:29,959 --> 00:52:32,393
- Leave me alone you dope fiend. Go away.

632
00:52:39,507 --> 00:52:41,107
- Mary.

633
00:52:41,107 --> 00:52:41,940
- Go away.

634
00:52:49,513 --> 00:52:52,346
(papers rustling)

635
00:53:03,300 --> 00:53:05,247
- [Professor] Okay.

636
00:53:05,247 --> 00:53:06,414
- [Penny] Hey.

637
00:53:08,630 --> 00:53:10,047
- [Professor] Ah.

638
00:53:13,357 --> 00:53:17,910
You're the last person
I ever expected to see.

639
00:53:17,910 --> 00:53:19,560
- [Penny] Okay, here's the thing.

640
00:53:21,210 --> 00:53:25,803
If something happens to me, I
want you to take care of Mary.

641
00:53:30,840 --> 00:53:32,040
What do you say to that?

642
00:53:33,870 --> 00:53:36,150
- What do you want me to say?

643
00:53:36,150 --> 00:53:38,913
Fine. Splendid. When shall I start?

644
00:53:40,650 --> 00:53:41,793
- No lecture, then?

645
00:53:43,822 --> 00:53:44,655
- You want one?

646
00:53:51,990 --> 00:53:53,370
- Maybe.

647
00:53:53,370 --> 00:53:54,220
- That's too bad.

648
00:53:56,160 --> 00:53:58,710
Penny, I'm bored telling you how worthy

649
00:53:58,710 --> 00:54:00,033
and talented you are.

650
00:54:06,150 --> 00:54:08,280
Go wreck yourself.

651
00:54:08,280 --> 00:54:11,163
Dinners will be much more
pleasant without you.

652
00:54:14,940 --> 00:54:19,323
- [Penny] When you called
that number and I showed up,

653
00:54:20,430 --> 00:54:23,193
you didn't expect all
this trouble, did you?

654
00:54:30,900 --> 00:54:35,103
- I thought I was looking
for sex. Something.

655
00:54:37,170 --> 00:54:38,947
But that's not what I found.

656
00:54:41,589 --> 00:54:43,256
- What did you find?

657
00:54:55,679 --> 00:54:58,179
- What happened to you, Penny?

658
00:55:00,131 --> 00:55:04,050
What turns a brilliant,

659
00:55:04,050 --> 00:55:08,993
brilliant girl into
this woman that you are?

660
00:55:21,185 --> 00:55:25,200
- You know how you can still see a star,

661
00:55:25,200 --> 00:55:26,583
long after it's dead?

662
00:55:28,230 --> 00:55:32,820
The light keeps coming,
and it's just an illusion.

663
00:55:32,820 --> 00:55:35,373
The star doesn't exist.

664
00:55:39,240 --> 00:55:41,673
- You exist.

665
00:55:47,010 --> 00:55:48,660
And I'm going to prove it to you.

666
00:55:51,424 --> 00:55:54,174
(ladder squeaks)

667
00:56:03,270 --> 00:56:05,133
Such a beautiful concept.

668
00:56:06,660 --> 00:56:09,243
Simple book of poetry about the sun.

669
00:56:14,555 --> 00:56:15,388
- May I?

670
00:56:20,939 --> 00:56:23,522
(gentle music)

671
00:56:36,547 --> 00:56:37,893
- "Listen, children,

672
00:56:39,120 --> 00:56:42,630
if you learn to touch
in the early morning,

673
00:56:42,630 --> 00:56:47,013
you will have brief
touchings and golden sunsets.

674
00:56:48,030 --> 00:56:53,030
Otherwise, I can only promise sunsets."

675
00:56:57,408 --> 00:57:00,075
(Mary laughing)

676
00:57:11,218 --> 00:57:13,263
- [Mary] All of it. It's too woo.

677
00:57:18,980 --> 00:57:21,843
- Hey. What are you doing?

678
00:57:22,710 --> 00:57:25,680
She's sick, you know? she
shouldn't be running around.

679
00:57:25,680 --> 00:57:26,973
- I'm feeling fine.

680
00:57:30,240 --> 00:57:31,683
- Please sit down with us.

681
00:57:36,720 --> 00:57:38,370
- [Mary] First you till the soil,

682
00:57:38,370 --> 00:57:40,410
and then you plant the seeds.

683
00:57:40,410 --> 00:57:41,340
When Penny was my age,

684
00:57:41,340 --> 00:57:44,790
she had ugly hair like
a boy, and no boobs.

685
00:57:44,790 --> 00:57:46,710
- So, what's changed?

686
00:57:46,710 --> 00:57:47,970
- Oh.

687
00:57:47,970 --> 00:57:49,080
- Sorry.

688
00:57:49,080 --> 00:57:52,203
And then you rub it over, but let it rain.

689
00:57:54,000 --> 00:57:56,610
And then what have you
got in the springtime?

690
00:57:56,610 --> 00:57:57,543
- A rash.

691
00:57:58,560 --> 00:57:59,703
- A rose garden.

692
00:58:00,663 --> 00:58:01,683
- A rash.

693
00:58:02,520 --> 00:58:03,390
- Rose garden.

694
00:58:03,390 --> 00:58:04,469
- Rash.
- Rose.

695
00:58:04,469 --> 00:58:05,420
- Rash.
- Rose.

696
00:58:05,420 --> 00:58:10,247
- Rash, rash, rash, rash, rash.

697
00:58:10,247 --> 00:58:12,300
- [Mary] Me and Penny
used to make up songs

698
00:58:12,300 --> 00:58:13,573
when we were little.

699
00:58:13,573 --> 00:58:17,737
I was Miss Mary Mac and
she was Miss Pennywhistle.

700
00:58:18,661 --> 00:58:21,270
- [Penny] Penny fell into a crack,

701
00:58:21,270 --> 00:58:23,850
picked up by Miss Mary Mac.

702
00:58:23,850 --> 00:58:26,366
Pocket pocket put it back.

703
00:58:26,366 --> 00:58:29,533
One cent, two cent, three cents smack.

704
00:58:32,733 --> 00:58:34,800
It's good to be a romantic, you know?

705
00:58:35,808 --> 00:58:37,983
She's a sucker for a happy ending.

706
00:58:44,010 --> 00:58:47,253
- Do you know that I've
never been on a date before?

707
00:58:48,090 --> 00:58:50,523
- No. There should be many boys.

708
00:58:53,880 --> 00:58:55,530
- Would you go on a date with me?

709
00:58:56,970 --> 00:58:57,803
- Mary.

710
00:58:59,490 --> 00:59:02,883
- I mean, if I was older.

711
00:59:04,356 --> 00:59:07,317
(Mary coughs)

712
00:59:07,317 --> 00:59:08,163
- You okay?

713
00:59:10,260 --> 00:59:13,147
- [Man] I will go on a
date with you right now.

714
00:59:14,610 --> 00:59:15,460
- [Penny] Really?

715
00:59:16,530 --> 00:59:17,730
Where will you take her?

716
00:59:18,650 --> 00:59:19,787
- To the cinema?

717
00:59:19,787 --> 00:59:20,620
- [Penny] No.

718
00:59:21,480 --> 00:59:23,403
Pretend you've never seen her before.

719
00:59:24,300 --> 00:59:29,300
You first see her at a Society Ball.

720
00:59:29,700 --> 00:59:31,263
- I'm a society lady.

721
00:59:32,130 --> 00:59:33,930
- And she's leaning against.

722
00:59:33,930 --> 00:59:36,090
No, pining-

723
00:59:36,090 --> 00:59:36,923
- Pining.

724
00:59:36,923 --> 00:59:40,863
- [Penny] By a clear, silvery fountain.

725
00:59:41,730 --> 00:59:43,710
What makes you wanna talk to her?

726
00:59:43,710 --> 00:59:48,710
- Oh, I would come to
her because she's lovely.

727
00:59:50,940 --> 00:59:54,780
And how do you say, mysterious?

728
00:59:54,780 --> 00:59:56,460
- [Mary] Oh no, you should never say that.

729
00:59:56,460 --> 00:59:59,130
You know why? American
girls don't like that.

730
00:59:59,130 --> 01:00:02,463
It's considered an insult
if you call them mysterious.

731
01:00:03,780 --> 01:00:07,323
- [Man] Enough, society lady.
We meet at a simple place.

732
01:00:08,190 --> 01:00:09,510
We meet on the bus.

733
01:00:09,510 --> 01:00:12,030
- And you're reading a book.

734
01:00:12,030 --> 01:00:13,380
- You are reading a book,

735
01:00:13,380 --> 01:00:17,586
and I sit beside you so
that you will speak to me,

736
01:00:17,586 --> 01:00:18,813
and I wait and I wait,
and you never speak to me.

737
01:00:22,321 --> 01:00:25,191
Then I say, "What is your name?"

738
01:00:25,191 --> 01:00:29,670
- And then I stand and I
say, "This is my stop."

739
01:00:29,670 --> 01:00:32,697
- Then I stand and say,
"This is our stop."

740
01:00:34,456 --> 01:00:35,289
- Oh, he's good.

741
01:00:36,630 --> 01:00:38,640
- I must see you again.

742
01:00:38,640 --> 01:00:41,553
My heart will die without you.

743
01:00:46,830 --> 01:00:47,663
- When?

744
01:00:48,540 --> 01:00:50,730
- I will tell you a day, Mary.

745
01:00:50,730 --> 01:00:55,473
And you will tell me this
is too soon. Or too late.

746
01:00:57,240 --> 01:00:58,073
Tomorrow.

747
01:01:02,910 --> 01:01:04,412
- Too late.

748
01:01:04,412 --> 01:01:06,995
(somber music)

749
01:01:12,472 --> 01:01:13,305
- Mary.

750
01:01:34,140 --> 01:01:34,973
- [Penny] Mary?

751
01:01:39,750 --> 01:01:40,583
Mary.

752
01:01:46,260 --> 01:01:48,360
That was nice, what you did.

753
01:01:48,360 --> 01:01:49,923
- Your sister makes me happy.

754
01:01:51,090 --> 01:01:51,923
- Yeah.

755
01:01:53,010 --> 01:01:53,843
- Wait.

756
01:01:55,020 --> 01:01:57,513
You are working tomorrow night?

757
01:01:59,702 --> 01:02:00,952
- I don't know.

758
01:02:02,153 --> 01:02:05,733
- I leave the store at nine
o'clock. You could meet me.

759
01:02:09,660 --> 01:02:10,493
- Maybe.

760
01:02:15,459 --> 01:02:16,292
Sweetie?

761
01:02:18,073 --> 01:02:20,490
(door slams)

762
01:02:25,896 --> 01:02:28,563
(Mary wheezing)

763
01:02:39,487 --> 01:02:43,904
(somber singing in foreign language)

764
01:03:08,307 --> 01:03:10,474
(gunfire)

765
01:03:23,588 --> 01:03:26,505
(grenade explodes)

766
01:03:40,737 --> 01:03:43,983
- Oh, please, please,
please come and meet me.

767
01:03:46,200 --> 01:03:47,073
- Monster.

768
01:03:48,810 --> 01:03:49,810
How are you feeling?

769
01:03:51,540 --> 01:03:52,373
- Kind of bad.

770
01:03:55,050 --> 01:03:56,650
- Yesterday was a good day, huh?

771
01:03:59,760 --> 01:04:00,963
You know it was.

772
01:04:06,000 --> 01:04:07,100
- So are you gonna go?

773
01:04:08,130 --> 01:04:09,480
- Where?

774
01:04:09,480 --> 01:04:10,313
- Meet him.

775
01:04:12,060 --> 01:04:13,263
- Why would I do that?

776
01:04:15,780 --> 01:04:17,313
He's your friend, not mine.

777
01:04:19,050 --> 01:04:20,103
Anyway, I gotta work.

778
01:04:24,205 --> 01:04:25,038
- Penny.

779
01:04:26,418 --> 01:04:29,001
(gentle music)

780
01:04:41,610 --> 01:04:44,277
(Mary coughing)

781
01:05:31,143 --> 01:05:34,920
- [Samuel] Dear Penny,
thank you for your letter

782
01:05:34,920 --> 01:05:35,883
and the poems.

783
01:05:37,560 --> 01:05:38,850
I'm kind of afraid of how you'll take

784
01:05:38,850 --> 01:05:40,150
what I've got to tell you.

785
01:05:41,568 --> 01:05:43,140
I want you to know,

786
01:05:43,140 --> 01:05:46,533
if I don't hear back from
you, I'll understand.

787
01:05:49,170 --> 01:05:51,840
I always meant to tell you about her.

788
01:05:51,840 --> 01:05:53,883
About what really happened.

789
01:05:54,990 --> 01:05:58,023
All the same, I'm afraid once you know,

790
01:06:02,070 --> 01:06:07,070
it may ruin your hopes for
our brilliant correspondence.

791
01:06:15,930 --> 01:06:18,093
- [Professor] You must
rescue my berilianda.

792
01:06:18,093 --> 01:06:20,970
Fell over in the wind and refuses to live.

793
01:06:20,970 --> 01:06:21,870
- I'll look at it.

794
01:06:29,790 --> 01:06:34,590
- So, the call of the wild
has once again deprived us

795
01:06:34,590 --> 01:06:36,453
of your sister's company.

796
01:06:39,900 --> 01:06:40,800
What does she eat?

797
01:06:41,880 --> 01:06:44,193
Nuts, berries that she
finds in the street.

798
01:06:45,690 --> 01:06:47,040
- I think Penny has a date.

799
01:06:50,640 --> 01:06:51,603
- Penny has a date?

800
01:06:54,750 --> 01:06:56,163
She actually likes somebody?

801
01:06:58,320 --> 01:07:00,120
- [Mary] We both like him very much.

802
01:07:08,042 --> 01:07:10,542
(Penny sighs)

803
01:07:11,460 --> 01:07:13,013
- [Professor] Read that book I gave you?

804
01:07:16,950 --> 01:07:17,783
Like it?

805
01:07:22,410 --> 01:07:23,947
My cooking really that bad?

806
01:07:27,950 --> 01:07:28,783
- No.

807
01:07:32,572 --> 01:07:34,045
- What?

808
01:07:34,045 --> 01:07:34,878
Hm?

809
01:07:36,482 --> 01:07:37,399
What is it?

810
01:07:39,190 --> 01:07:41,773
- I guess it's a lot of things.

811
01:07:44,314 --> 01:07:46,981
(pager beeping)

812
01:07:49,085 --> 01:07:52,252
(gentle somber music)

813
01:08:21,215 --> 01:08:23,798
- Is this really what you want?

814
01:08:34,347 --> 01:08:36,930
- [Professor] I'm not letting
you go home by yourself.

815
01:08:36,930 --> 01:08:39,600
- I'll be fine. I need the air.

816
01:08:39,600 --> 01:08:41,200
I can manage four blocks.

817
01:08:41,200 --> 01:08:44,078
- No, there's no
question. I'm driving you.

818
01:08:44,078 --> 01:08:47,207
- I'm not a baby, Professor.
I can do things for myself.

819
01:08:49,694 --> 01:08:52,111
(door slams)

820
01:08:58,092 --> 01:09:01,009
(skeleton rattles)

821
01:09:02,936 --> 01:09:05,474
(Mary coughs)

822
01:09:05,474 --> 01:09:07,974
(eerie music)

823
01:09:14,358 --> 01:09:17,191
(muffled chatter)

824
01:09:23,170 --> 01:09:27,003
- [Penny] Hey baby, I've
been waiting for you.

825
01:09:29,791 --> 01:09:31,291
Come on over here.

826
01:09:37,736 --> 01:09:40,153
- [Distorted Voice] Hey baby.

827
01:09:41,019 --> 01:09:43,686
(ominous music)

828
01:09:49,309 --> 01:09:51,976
(Mary coughing)

829
01:10:02,957 --> 01:10:05,540
(pot shatters)

830
01:10:25,998 --> 01:10:26,831
- Oh.

831
01:10:36,241 --> 01:10:37,908
- [Professor] Penny.

832
01:10:41,340 --> 01:10:42,390
- Is this the sister?

833
01:10:43,860 --> 01:10:45,420
- Where is she? Can I see her?

834
01:10:45,420 --> 01:10:47,280
- [Doctor] Yes. For a short time only.

835
01:10:47,280 --> 01:10:49,050
She has a collapsed lung.

836
01:10:49,050 --> 01:10:51,360
Have you not been
monitoring her condition?

837
01:10:51,360 --> 01:10:52,760
- Please can I just see her?

838
01:10:58,184 --> 01:11:01,101
(machines beeping)

839
01:11:03,209 --> 01:11:05,792
(somber music)

840
01:11:06,990 --> 01:11:09,060
- [Professor] Penny, if you
elect to destroy your mind

841
01:11:09,060 --> 01:11:10,193
and your body-
- Oh, not now.

842
01:11:10,193 --> 01:11:12,390
- That is your right.
Mary may accept that.

843
01:11:12,390 --> 01:11:13,223
She may deny that.

844
01:11:13,223 --> 01:11:15,213
- Where were you when this happened?

845
01:11:16,890 --> 01:11:17,740
- Where were you?

846
01:11:20,220 --> 01:11:21,053
Do you understand

847
01:11:21,053 --> 01:11:23,190
that what is happening
to your sister is real?

848
01:11:23,190 --> 01:11:24,543
This is her life.

849
01:11:26,100 --> 01:11:29,550
That when you elect to take
yourself back to the gutter,

850
01:11:29,550 --> 01:11:32,490
to drug yourself and abstain from reality,

851
01:11:32,490 --> 01:11:34,023
you are abandoning her.

852
01:11:36,030 --> 01:11:38,800
And I will not let you make that mistake.

853
01:11:55,259 --> 01:11:57,842
(Mary wheezes)

854
01:12:07,663 --> 01:12:08,580
- I'm here.

855
01:12:18,759 --> 01:12:21,509
(dramatic music)

856
01:12:44,331 --> 01:12:47,331
- [Penny] Good morning, sleepy girl.

857
01:12:48,680 --> 01:12:49,513
- Hey.

858
01:12:53,002 --> 01:12:53,835
- Hey.

859
01:12:56,294 --> 01:12:58,044
- Will you bring my book Next time?

860
01:13:00,330 --> 01:13:01,163
- Yeah.

861
01:13:06,300 --> 01:13:07,133
Look at you.

862
01:13:09,905 --> 01:13:11,072
- Look at you.

863
01:13:12,240 --> 01:13:14,043
- I was working late.

864
01:13:15,240 --> 01:13:16,073
- Sure.

865
01:13:17,280 --> 01:13:18,830
And I'm the Princess of Persia.

866
01:13:21,300 --> 01:13:22,173
- Comedian.

867
01:13:36,570 --> 01:13:38,313
Have you been waiting here for me?

868
01:13:41,400 --> 01:13:42,500
- [Man] Where is Mary?

869
01:13:43,530 --> 01:13:44,853
- She's in the hospital.

870
01:13:46,530 --> 01:13:49,893
- [Man] I have found my
family. I'm leaving here soon.

871
01:13:53,343 --> 01:13:56,010
(Mary coughing)

872
01:14:06,830 --> 01:14:09,497
(Mary wheezing)

873
01:14:18,390 --> 01:14:19,613
- Happy birthday, Mary.

874
01:14:25,650 --> 01:14:26,483
Open.

875
01:14:35,700 --> 01:14:36,730
- What is this?

876
01:14:38,363 --> 01:14:42,603
- For the society lady.
By the silver fountain.

877
01:14:44,640 --> 01:14:45,473
- Thank you.

878
01:14:51,273 --> 01:14:52,653
It's nice and big.

879
01:15:00,390 --> 01:15:01,690
You're leaving aren't you?

880
01:15:04,410 --> 01:15:05,243
- Yes.

881
01:15:06,750 --> 01:15:08,770
I can't just say goodbye.

882
01:15:10,253 --> 01:15:11,853
- Are you ever coming back?

883
01:15:15,780 --> 01:15:16,613
- I don't know.

884
01:15:21,066 --> 01:15:24,817
- Well that's too bad, because
once I get out of here,

885
01:15:25,800 --> 01:15:28,233
I was gonna ask you on a date.

886
01:15:32,414 --> 01:15:37,363
- I would've said yes.

887
01:15:37,363 --> 01:15:39,477
- I would've worn the dress.

888
01:15:41,820 --> 01:15:42,820
- Of course.

889
01:15:47,503 --> 01:15:49,003
- I would've said,

890
01:15:49,941 --> 01:15:54,441
(Mary and man speak foreign language)

891
01:16:03,600 --> 01:16:05,225
- [Receptionist] Dr. Kravitz,

892
01:16:05,225 --> 01:16:06,960
you have a visitor in the main lobby.

893
01:16:06,960 --> 01:16:10,490
Dr. Kravitz, a visitor in the main lobby.

894
01:16:16,893 --> 01:16:18,693
- What are you guys doing?

895
01:16:19,543 --> 01:16:20,710
- [Penny] Ssh.

896
01:16:23,160 --> 01:16:24,610
- [Mary] Are you almost done?

897
01:16:26,528 --> 01:16:28,950
(gentle whimsical music)

898
01:16:28,950 --> 01:16:29,783
- [Penny] Here.

899
01:16:35,664 --> 01:16:38,331
(Mary wheezing)

900
01:16:51,060 --> 01:16:53,417
- Happy birthday.
- Happy birthday.

901
01:16:55,140 --> 01:16:55,990
- Do you like it?

902
01:16:58,611 --> 01:17:00,833
I know it's not as good as the beach.

903
01:17:06,391 --> 01:17:07,391
Make a wish.

904
01:17:10,027 --> 01:17:13,407
(Mary gasping)

905
01:17:13,407 --> 01:17:15,574
- We should call somebody.

906
01:17:16,443 --> 01:17:17,943
- Are you alright?

907
01:17:27,102 --> 01:17:27,935
Mary?

908
01:17:32,047 --> 01:17:33,380
Are you alright?

909
01:17:38,487 --> 01:17:39,904
- Yeah, I'm okay.

910
01:17:48,082 --> 01:17:50,749
(comet hissing)

911
01:17:52,268 --> 01:17:54,935
(Mary wheezing)

912
01:18:03,149 --> 01:18:06,982
- [Mary] This is what
I'm gonna miss the most.

913
01:18:08,636 --> 01:18:09,469
- What?

914
01:18:14,368 --> 01:18:15,451
- You and me.

915
01:18:19,351 --> 01:18:21,834
(seagulls squawk)

916
01:18:21,834 --> 01:18:25,558
Penny, there's a story I wanna tell you.

917
01:18:25,558 --> 01:18:26,975
It's about a man,

918
01:18:30,443 --> 01:18:33,393
and how he loved this woman very much,

919
01:18:37,080 --> 01:18:39,093
and they were going to get married.

920
01:18:40,980 --> 01:18:45,980
Only, it turned out the
woman got very, very sick.

921
01:18:47,250 --> 01:18:52,113
They said without her
treatments, she will quickly die.

922
01:18:55,470 --> 01:18:56,770
- Who told you this story?

923
01:18:59,160 --> 01:18:59,993
- Just listen.

924
01:19:02,160 --> 01:19:06,273
So he did the only thing he knew to do,

925
01:19:07,334 --> 01:19:12,334
he took her away from the
hospital and the awful treatments.

926
01:19:13,230 --> 01:19:16,513
But he was scared.

927
01:19:16,513 --> 01:19:17,346
- [Samuel] I was afraid.

928
01:19:17,346 --> 01:19:18,570
- They both knew that-

929
01:19:18,570 --> 01:19:19,666
- [Samuel] Both knew she
didn't have much time.

930
01:19:19,666 --> 01:19:22,427
- [Mary] She didn't have much time.

931
01:19:22,427 --> 01:19:24,483
- [Samuel] And then, she asked me,

932
01:19:25,950 --> 01:19:27,933
take her to her special place.

933
01:19:29,520 --> 01:19:34,153
It was this beautiful waterfall
where we fell in love.

934
01:19:34,153 --> 01:19:38,160
I was far away from the
hospital, but I took her,

935
01:19:38,160 --> 01:19:39,363
'cause she asked me to.

936
01:19:42,845 --> 01:19:44,160
And we got out of the car and stood again

937
01:19:44,160 --> 01:19:45,410
on the edge of the falls.

938
01:19:47,640 --> 01:19:49,563
She just stood there real still,

939
01:19:50,730 --> 01:19:53,100
looking out over the edge for a long time.

940
01:19:53,100 --> 01:19:54,900
- [Mary] I started to worry about her.

941
01:19:54,900 --> 01:19:56,370
- [Samuel] I started to worry about her.

942
01:19:56,370 --> 01:19:59,280
- [Mary] She was gonna
do something crazy, like-

943
01:19:59,280 --> 01:20:00,863
- [Samuel] Jump off.
- [Mary] Jump off.

944
01:20:04,230 --> 01:20:06,093
- Did she? Did she jump?

945
01:20:08,940 --> 01:20:10,560
- No.

946
01:20:10,560 --> 01:20:15,560
She died his arms, and he
was charged with manslaughter

947
01:20:17,160 --> 01:20:21,060
for kidnapping her away
from all the doctors

948
01:20:21,060 --> 01:20:24,750
and hospitals and pain.

949
01:20:33,000 --> 01:20:35,000
But on the edge of that beautiful place,

950
01:20:37,290 --> 01:20:41,013
she looked at him and said,

951
01:20:43,147 --> 01:20:44,823
"Don't feel sorry for me.

952
01:20:47,558 --> 01:20:48,508
I am the lucky one.

953
01:20:51,383 --> 01:20:56,177
Other people live in doubt
and pain all their lives.

954
01:20:58,512 --> 01:21:03,512
But I know my love will last forever.

955
01:21:12,313 --> 01:21:13,743
- I like that story.

956
01:21:16,530 --> 01:21:18,780
You should try to get
some sleep, little one.

957
01:21:19,740 --> 01:21:20,890
See you in the morning.

958
01:21:38,160 --> 01:21:41,100
- [Receptionist] Dr.
Flores, dial 118, please.

959
01:21:41,100 --> 01:21:44,043
Dr. Flores, can you please dial 118.

960
01:21:48,810 --> 01:21:49,643
- Penny?

961
01:21:53,485 --> 01:21:55,257
- What?

962
01:21:55,257 --> 01:21:56,853
- I'm a friend of Kristjan's.

963
01:21:58,444 --> 01:21:59,277
- Who?

964
01:22:00,420 --> 01:22:01,413
- Your neighbor.

965
01:22:03,041 --> 01:22:06,540
- Oh.

966
01:22:06,540 --> 01:22:07,373
What is it?

967
01:22:08,280 --> 01:22:10,320
- He asked me to bring you this address

968
01:22:10,320 --> 01:22:12,820
where you can write to him
in Hungary if you want.

969
01:22:15,810 --> 01:22:17,823
He leaves today on the bus.

970
01:22:29,945 --> 01:22:33,362
(somber whimsical music)

971
01:22:43,920 --> 01:22:44,753
- Kristjan?

972
01:22:48,090 --> 01:22:50,790
Oh my God. I was afraid
you'd already gone.

973
01:22:50,790 --> 01:22:52,590
- This is my bus.

974
01:22:52,590 --> 01:22:54,660
- I wanted to say goodbye,

975
01:22:54,660 --> 01:22:57,780
and I'm sorry.

976
01:22:57,780 --> 01:22:58,653
I never.

977
01:23:02,479 --> 01:23:03,750
I wanted to be your friend.

978
01:23:03,750 --> 01:23:05,160
- [Kristjan] You are my friend.

979
01:23:05,160 --> 01:23:08,515
- But I never even knew your name.

980
01:23:08,515 --> 01:23:10,913
- [Tannoy] Last call for eastbound bus 12.

981
01:23:10,913 --> 01:23:12,346
- Oh God, please.

982
01:23:12,346 --> 01:23:17,346
- I know, I know.

983
01:23:18,660 --> 01:23:23,073
These things, Penny,
the pain in your heart.

984
01:23:24,150 --> 01:23:27,453
What's happening to Mary,
you must forgive yourself.

985
01:23:30,515 --> 01:23:31,693
- I don't think that I can.

986
01:23:33,575 --> 01:23:34,408
- You can.

987
01:23:36,508 --> 01:23:37,341
You can.

988
01:23:40,449 --> 01:23:41,699
Goodbye, Penny.

989
01:23:43,301 --> 01:23:46,218
(melancholy music)

990
01:24:08,757 --> 01:24:10,860
- [Doctor] I'm sorry to
have to tell you this,

991
01:24:10,860 --> 01:24:12,819
but there's nothing more that we can do.

992
01:24:12,819 --> 01:24:13,768
- Can we see her now?

993
01:24:13,768 --> 01:24:15,570
- Yes. Go on in.

994
01:24:15,570 --> 01:24:16,987
- You'll be okay.

995
01:24:23,126 --> 01:24:26,017
(machines beeping)

996
01:24:26,017 --> 01:24:28,434
(Mary gasps)

997
01:24:51,399 --> 01:24:52,899
- Hey, angel girl.

998
01:24:56,070 --> 01:24:57,903
- I finished our book.

999
01:25:16,959 --> 01:25:18,376
- It's beautiful.

1000
01:25:28,779 --> 01:25:31,696
- Will you tell me about the beach?

1001
01:25:35,225 --> 01:25:36,058
- Okay.

1002
01:25:36,938 --> 01:25:41,938
We lived there year round,

1003
01:25:44,606 --> 01:25:46,356
with our mom and dad.

1004
01:25:52,200 --> 01:25:53,493
In the wintertime.

1005
01:25:54,532 --> 01:25:57,115
(gentle music)

1006
01:26:02,336 --> 01:26:04,753
- Promise me you'll still go.

1007
01:26:18,690 --> 01:26:20,370
We're getting too big for this.

1008
01:26:26,172 --> 01:26:28,172
- Don't let this happen.

1009
01:26:29,636 --> 01:26:31,469
Don't let this happen.

1010
01:26:39,324 --> 01:26:42,407
- [Mary] What do you think he dreams?

1011
01:26:43,838 --> 01:26:44,671
- Who?

1012
01:26:46,839 --> 01:26:49,422
- Up there, all alone in space?

1013
01:26:53,210 --> 01:26:54,460
- [Penny] Baby.

1014
01:26:57,780 --> 01:27:00,530
He's probably dreaming about you.

1015
01:27:09,987 --> 01:27:12,570
(Mary wheezes)

1016
01:27:44,605 --> 01:27:48,522
(machines beeping frantically)

1017
01:27:53,569 --> 01:27:56,986
(gentle whimsical music)

1018
01:28:41,710 --> 01:28:44,710
(prolonged beeping)

1019
01:29:03,371 --> 01:29:06,121
(wind whistling)

1020
01:29:28,007 --> 01:29:30,757
(child giggling)

1021
01:29:41,159 --> 01:29:43,470
- [Child] How do you think she died?

1022
01:29:43,470 --> 01:29:44,370
- Looks like she drowned.

1023
01:29:44,370 --> 01:29:45,420
- We should bury her.

1024
01:29:49,505 --> 01:29:52,172
(child squeals)

1025
01:30:04,560 --> 01:30:07,774
- Who are you?

1026
01:30:07,774 --> 01:30:08,607
- Who are you?

1027
01:30:10,470 --> 01:30:11,463
- Can we have more?

1028
01:30:12,870 --> 01:30:13,703
- More what?

1029
01:30:14,700 --> 01:30:15,753
- Stars.

1030
01:30:18,540 --> 01:30:20,370
- [Penny] That's mine.

1031
01:30:20,370 --> 01:30:22,357
- I wasn't gonna steal it.

1032
01:30:22,357 --> 01:30:23,607
I was just looking at it.

1033
01:30:29,405 --> 01:30:30,572
- Is that you?

1034
01:30:34,890 --> 01:30:36,017
- That's my sister.

1035
01:30:42,973 --> 01:30:45,723
(child laughing)

1036
01:30:48,709 --> 01:30:51,490
- Another cartwheel, okay?

1037
01:30:51,490 --> 01:30:54,907
(gentle uplifting music)

1038
01:31:35,338 --> 01:31:36,338
- [Man] Hey.

1039
01:31:38,730 --> 01:31:39,980
You're Penny, aren't you?

1040
01:31:41,310 --> 01:31:42,143
- Yeah.

1041
01:31:43,260 --> 01:31:44,433
- I saved your letters.

1042
01:31:48,960 --> 01:31:50,710
Oh, no, I didn't mean to scare you.

1043
01:31:53,131 --> 01:31:54,579
I shouldn't have come.

1044
01:31:54,579 --> 01:31:55,662
- [Penny] No.

1045
01:31:56,712 --> 01:31:57,545
No.

1046
01:32:02,129 --> 01:32:02,962
Please.

1047
01:32:04,440 --> 01:32:05,273
Stay.

1048
01:32:09,912 --> 01:32:12,162
I forgot about the letters.

1049
01:32:30,958 --> 01:32:32,823
- They made contact yesterday.

1050
01:32:34,290 --> 01:32:35,700
- What?

1051
01:32:35,700 --> 01:32:38,253
- The astronaut that you wrote me about.

1052
01:32:39,990 --> 01:32:42,840
He's coming back around the sun.

1053
01:32:42,840 --> 01:32:46,650
They can finally talk to him again.

1054
01:32:46,650 --> 01:32:47,483
- The astronaut?

1055
01:32:53,400 --> 01:32:54,543
So, how was he then?

1056
01:32:58,590 --> 01:32:59,790
When they talked to him?

1057
01:33:02,940 --> 01:33:07,940
- Kind of crazy, they said, but alive.

1058
01:33:20,220 --> 01:33:23,103
- [Penny] Now, I know why
Mary made the Book of Stars.

1059
01:33:24,060 --> 01:33:26,520
Every time I turn these pages,

1060
01:33:26,520 --> 01:33:28,203
I think about what she taught me.

1061
01:33:29,670 --> 01:33:31,863
The best gifts are given in secret,

1062
01:33:32,910 --> 01:33:36,640
and each of us writes our own endings.

1063
01:33:37,563 --> 01:33:40,146
(mellow music)

